\pard\plain\s0\qj\widctlpar\f0\fs20\sl240\slmult1 \sb60 \fi0 In what follows the paragraph signs \ldblquote \'a7\rdblquote  refer to the paragraphs in Halmos\rquote  \ldblquote Finite-Dimensional Vector Spaces.\rdblquote  The more physically oriented notation in Mermin\rquote s book on quantum information theory 
[{\field{\*\fldinst{\lang1024 REF BIB_mermin_04 \\* MERGEFORMAT }}{\fldrslt{{90}{2002-2008}{{Mermin}}{{}}}}}, {\field{\*\fldinst{\lang1024 REF BIB_mermin_07 \\* MERGEFORMAT }}{\fldrslt{{91}{2007}{{Mermin}}{{}}}}}
] is adopted. Vectors are typed in bold face. The overline sign stands for complex conjugation; that is, if {